Consider an application, StudentMangementSystem, that retrieves the student details from the database for the given student ID. For any invalid student ID, the application throws a necessary business exception that would be handled by the ControllerAdvice.

Which of the following code snippets can be used to handle the exception 'StudentManagementException' thrown out in the above scenario?

" @ControllerAdvice public class ErrorHandlingController { @ExceptionHandler(StudentManagementException.class) public final ResponseEntity invalidEntry(Exception e) { // Return the response } } "
" @ControllerAdvice @ExceptionHandler(StudentManagementException.class) public class ErrorHandlingController { public final ResponseEntity invalidEntry(Exception e) { // Return the response } } "
"public class ErrorHandlingController { @ControllerAdvice(StudentManagementException.class) public final ResponseEntity invalidEntry(Exception e) { // Return the response } } "
"public class ErrorHandlingController extends ControllerAdvice { public final ResponseEntity invalidEntry(Exception e) { // Return the response } } "
